First Lady Melania Trump and Second Lady Karen Pence visited Charleston, South Carolina to thank troops for their service and learn about the base's emergency response efforts. They visited Lambs Elementary School, where they participated in the Red Cross Pillowcase Project, an emergency preparedness program for children. They also visited the Emergency Operations Center on base and received briefings from various agencies on disaster readiness and response. Mrs. Trump addressed troops and civilians at Joint Base Charleston, highlighting the humanitarian efforts taking place within the community and reaffirming support for the military. Both ladies expressed gratitude for the warm welcome and praised the Red Cross and Lambs Elementary for teaching emergency preparedness skills to children.